  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accountant (6-Month Contract Role)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Introduction</strong><br />This is a <strong>6-month contract role</strong> to cover a <strong>maternity leave</strong> period. The Accountant will support the finance team in managing consolidation, reporting, and coordination with overseas subsidiaries to ensure smooth financial operations during the incumbent’s absence.<br /><br /><strong>Company Overview</strong><br />Our Vision is to become a leading integrated logistics service provider in the region, offering efficient, reliable and quality warehousing and logistics support to the local and overseas market by leveraging on technology and operational excellence.<br /><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Oversee the accounts of a few entities, namely Holdings company, two dormant investment holdings companies, and a subsidiary.</p></li><li><p>Lead and provide guidance to the subordinates for accounts closing for Holdings company and the subsidiary.</p></li><li><p>Preparation of monthly Management Reports for the two dormant investment holdings companies.</p></li><li><p>Assist the manager in the preparation of consolidated financial statement.</p></li><li><p>Assist in liaison with overseas subsidiaries.</p></li><li><p>Other ad-hoc assignment.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Minimum Qualifications & Experience Required</strong></p><ul><li><p>Degree holder or equivalent in Accountancy.</p></li><li><p>At least 2 years of relevant working experience in a similar capacity.</p></li><li><p>Possess a good working attitude, strong analytical skills, and a strong sense of responsibility.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Company Benefits at a Glance:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Daily Lunch Provided</p></li><li><p>Company Transport Provided at designated MRT stations (Lakeside, Boon Lay & Woodlands)</p></li></ul>",
